Sentencas: The structural and electrochemical properties of the layered perovskite oxides LaSrC1-xSbxO4 (0 <= x <= 0.20) were investigated to study the effects of substituting Sb for Co for application as cathode materials in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of crystal structure analyses show the maximum content of Sb in LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 to be 0.05 as a pure single phase.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XPS shows that Co and Sb in LaSrCo0.95Sb0.05O4 may possess mixed-oxidation states.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity increased greatly after Sb substitution.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An improvement in the cathode polarization (R-p) values is observed from the Sb-doped sample with respect to the undoped samples.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For example, R-p of LaSrCo0.95Sb0.05O4 on LSGM was observed to be 0.16 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The main rate-limiting step for LaSrCo0.95Sb0.05O4 cathode is charge transfer of oxygen atoms.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that Sb can be incorporated into LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 based materials and can have a beneficial effect on the performance, making them potentially suitable for use as cathode materials in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Investigation of structural and electrochemical properties of LaSrCo1-xSbxO4 (0≤x≤0.20) as potential cathode materials in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
